SUMMARY: JSON.stringify()
What does it do?
It converts a JavaScript object into a JSON string.

Why use it?
Because you cannot send objects to APIs / databases / files.
You must send string format.

Before: Object (cannot send to API)

let user = {
    name: 'hs',
    age: 25
}

After: JSON String (can send to API)

let jsonStr = JSON.stringify(user);
console.log(jsonStr)

output:     '{"name":"hs","age":25}'

